It's apparently cold today.

153
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:03,550
Have a nice day, then.

154
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:08,560
 ...the way Yoon Bok looks at me. 

155
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:14,790
♫  It seems like a dream in one last  ♫

156
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:19,330
♫  It seems like a dream in one last  ♫

157
00:13:19,330 --> 00:13:23,610
Why did he put the scarf on me? Why?

158
00:13:23,610 --> 00:13:25,670
It's his scarf.

159
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:28,240
Why did he put it on me?

160
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:37,800
♫  I looked for you everywhere  ♫

161
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:42,140
By chance, does he like me?

162
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:44,570
My gosh. Gosh!

163
00:13:46,530 --> 00:13:49,260
That can't be.

164
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:54,090
Maybe he decided to be friendlier as a student.

165
00:13:54,090 --> 00:14:01,530
♫  When I hold you in my arms  ♫

166
00:14:01,530 --> 00:14:03,650
What's going on?

167
00:14:03,650 --> 00:14:06,010
I'm getting a scent of a man from you.

168
00:14:06,010 --> 00:14:07,270
Pardon?

169
00:14:07,270 --> 00:14:09,380
What do you mean?

170
00:14:09,380 --> 00:14:11,800
Did you get a boyfriend?

171
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,060
That can't be.

172
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:16,170
Who put the scarf on you, then?

173
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:19,160
I did. I put it on myself.

174
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:22,210
Hong Do put it on Hong Do.

175
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:29,830
First of all, I approve of his taste.

176
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:53,430
 I will free myself... 

177
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,890
 from preserving tradition, 

178
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:58,560
 inheriting the village, or getting married! 

179
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:03,590
 I will not do anything you planned for me. 

180
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:07,120
 As Mother told me to, 

181
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:10,360
 I will do what I want to do... 

182
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,520
 and live freely from now on. 

183
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:29,590
Master, this is Yoon Ah.

184
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:31,530
 Come in. 

185
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:40,280
How is Yoon Bok doing?

186
00:15:40,860 --> 00:15:43,750
Since the funeral,

187
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:47,190
he has been living with Lady Yi Bok.

188
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:50,540
Yes.

189
00:15:50,540 --> 00:15:55,590
He needs time to feel comforted since he went through a lot.

190
00:15:56,450 --> 00:16:01,560
You should help him get back to where he belongs soon.

191
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:05,540
- Yes, sir. 
 - Stop by and update me often.

192
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:06,930
Yes, sir.

193
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:35,580
He must be worn out physically and mentally grieving.

194
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:38,950
You should take good care of him, Yoon Ah.

195
00:16:38,950 --> 00:16:42,470
- I will. 
 - Is he feeling sick at all?

196
00:16:42,470 --> 00:16:45,020
He does not appear to be sick.

197
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:48,130
Is he not having a hard time?

198
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:52,190
He does not appear to be.

199
00:16:52,190 --> 00:16:53,920
But he has been kind of strange.

200
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:56,590
Why? Is something wrong with him?

201
00:16:56,590 --> 00:16:59,240
No, no. It is not like that.

202
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:01,830
He just changed a bit.

203
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:05,270
- What do you mean? 
 - He just...

204
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,710
did.

205
00:17:08,610 --> 00:17:10,310
Yes.

206
00:17:10,310 --> 00:17:14,420
Anyway, he is not his old self anymore.

207
00:17:27,930 --> 00:17:29,980
Yoon Bok.

208
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,330
Teacher.

209
00:17:34,330 --> 00:17:36,400
What are you doing here?

210
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:40,560
Artist Kim told me to draw that.

211
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:47,780
How was your day?

212
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:49,640
Did you stay warm?

213
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,990
Yes, thanks to you.

214
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,820
Have you had dinner?

215
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:59,450
Not yet.

216
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:01,470
Have you eaten?

217
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:04,710
I have not yet, either.

218
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,910
Should we eat together, then?

219
00:18:13,910 --> 00:18:15,370
Yes!

220
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:18,510
Yes.

221
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:32,890
 He has no issue sharing a table anymore, either. 

222
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:41,070
Teacher,

223
00:18:43,420 --> 00:18:45,210
eat more.

224
00:18:46,010 --> 00:18:49,260
Okay, thank you.

225
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:58,710
 By chance, am I fooling myself 

226
00:18:58,710 --> 00:19:01,610
 because I like Yoon Bok so much? 

227
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:42,800
 - By chance...  
 - Where's a plate...

228
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,980
Do you want a plate?

229
00:19:50,050 --> 00:19:52,170
I will get it.

230
00:20:16,330 --> 00:20:20,530
 No. To say I'm fooling myself, 

231
00:20:20,530 --> 00:20:24,360
 Yoon Bok is acting too out of the ordinary. 

232
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,740
Teacher,

233
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:36,110
please sit here.

234
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:38,970
- Next to you? 
 - Yes.

235
00:20:38,970 --> 00:20:40,550
Okay.

236
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,780
 By chance... 

237
00:20:50,780 --> 00:20:53,900
 does Yoon Bok really like me? 

238
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:57,020
Teacher, please have some.

239
00:20:58,350 --> 00:21:00,240
Thank you.

240
00:21:00,740 --> 00:21:03,890
- You should have some, too. 
 - Please go ahead.

241
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:11,280
Fine. Here.

242
00:21:14,620 --> 00:21:18,100
He's a student who cares for his teacher. My student.

243
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,080
He's being polite, you know.

244
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:23,330
I say, "Be." You say, "Polite."

245
00:21:34,410 --> 00:21:37,710
Maybe you got sick because you've been through a lot.

246
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:40,240
Take care of yourself.

247
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,290
Is it because I'm tired?

248
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,440
Here.

249
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:04,820
You used to want this whenever you got sick.

250
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:10,590
Mom used to make this for me.

251
00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:12,830
Eat it while it's hot.

252
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,730
Thank you.

253
00:22:23,790 --> 00:22:25,570
Let me do it.

254
00:22:25,570 --> 00:22:27,990
It was a lot of work to make that.

255
00:22:27,990 --> 00:22:30,700
So make sure to finish it.

256
00:22:43,180 --> 00:22:47,860
Sitting here like this reminds me of the old days.

257
00:22:50,790 --> 00:22:54,470
We were so happy then.

258
00:22:54,470 --> 00:22:56,190
Right?

259
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,080
 You bastard! 

260
00:23:56,080 --> 00:24:01,180
 How dare you make the precious child sick? 

261
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,610
I'm glad...

262
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:14,000
that it's a happy memory for you.

263
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:19,970
 To me, it was a scar I couldn't recover from. 

264
00:25:00,340 --> 00:25:04,680
The villagers are complaining about your scream every night.

265
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:08,580
I told you to open their hearts, but you only open their eardrums.

266
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:09,970
Try living there for a day.

267
00:25:09,970 --> 00:25:12,410
See if you can help screaming.

268
00:25:12,410 --> 00:25:16,390
I don't know where the cuckoo is, either.

269
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:21,320
That is why I got you a room in the Woorim House.

270
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:24,200
Stay here from now on. Make yourself at—

271
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:27,640
I'll make myself at home, then.

272
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:31,450
This room is in much better condition.

273
00:25:38,310 --> 00:25:40,080
Right.

